external_knowledge:
- "shining stars" refers to users who are highly engaged, as measured by their interactions and course enrollments;
- "combined engagement" is the sum of the ranks of interactions and enrollments;
- "top 10 users" refers to the users with the lowest combined engagement rank, indicating the highest level of engagement.

- "stars in the constellation" refers to users in the database;
- "danced together" refers to interactions between users;
- "celestial period from January to February 2023" refers to the date range from January 1, 2023, to February 28, 2023;
- "more than once" means more than one interaction.

- 'Top 3 most popular courses' refers to the courses with the highest number of enrollments;
- 'Enrollment count' is the number of students enrolled in the course;
- 'Interaction count' is the total number of interactions recorded for the course;
- 'Feedback count' is the total number of feedback entries received for the course;
- 'Average rating' is the mean rating of the course based on feedback.

- "Courses have blossomed with multiple pieces of feedback" means the courses have more than one feedback entry;
- "Gardeners (users) that have tended to them" refers to the users who have provided feedback;
- "Average rating of the blooms" means the average rating of the course.

sql:
SELECT AVG(f.rating) AS average_course_rating
FROM feedback f
JOIN course_enrollments ce ON f.user_id = ce.user_id AND f.course_id = ce.course_id;

SELECT AVG(c.progress) AS average_enrollment_progress
FROM course_enrollments c
JOIN feedback f ON c.user_id = f.user_id AND c.course_id = f.course_id;

external_knowledge:
- Active instructors are those whose account status is 'active' and have logged in at least once.;
- The role 'Instructor' is a specific role in the system, identified by a unique `role_id` in the `roles` table.;
- Enrolled users are those who have an entry in the `course_enrollments` table, indicating they have registered for at least one course.

- "Top 3 most engaged users" refers to users with the highest number of interactions;
- "Provided feedback" means users have at least one feedback entry;
- "Course enrollments and completions" include the course name, enrollment date, completion date, and certificate issuance status.

- 'trailblazers' refers to users who have completed courses;
- 'navigating the digital landscape' refers to the total duration of interactions;
- 10 hours = 600 minutes.

- "Interactions" include various types like views, comments, and completions.;
- "Duration" is measured in minutes.;
- "Cumulative duration" is the total time spent by a user across all their interactions with a course.
